Both the 3.8 L and 4.0 L engines were paired with Chrysler's 62TE 6-speed automatic transmission with variable line pressure (VLP) technology (See [[Ultradrive#62TE]]).

In Canada (2008–2010) the 3.3 L was the standard engine across the range, combined with the 4-speed 41TE automatic transmission. The 4.0 L engine and six-speed combination was available as an option on only the top of the range SXT models. In 2011 the six-speed transmission was specified as standard on the [[Chrysler Town & Country|Town & Country]].

===Safety===
In the U.S. the [[National Highway Traffic Safety Administration]]'s (NHTSA) New Car Assessment Program crash testing, the 2010 Dodge Grand Caravan achieved a five star (top safety) rating in several categories.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.safercar.gov/portal/site/safercar/ |title=2010 Chrysler minivan US NCAP safety ratings |work=NHTSA www.Safercar.gov |accessdate=June 23, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100522231124/http://www.safercar.gov/portal/site/safercar/ |archivedate=May 22, 2010 |df=mdy }}</ref>

