=== Volkswagen Routan ===
{{main|Volkswagen Routan}}
[[File:Routan.jpg|thumb|Volkswagen Routan SE]]
Beginning with Generation V, Volkswagen began marketing the Volkswagen Routan, a [[badge engineering|rebadged]] variant of the [[Chrysler minivans|Chrysler RT platform]] minivan with revised styling and content, for the North American market. The original contract between Chrysler and Volkswagen called for five years of production (through 2013).<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.automobilemag.com/news/report-volkswagen-routan-minivan-production-ends-191045/ |title=Report: Volkswagen Routan Minivan Production Halted Temporarily |first=Jake |last=Holmes |date=December 12, 2012 |work=Automobile magazine |accessdate= April 4, 2016}}</ref>

The Routan, made at [[Windsor Assembly]] alongside the Grand Caravan, debuted in 2008 at the Chicago Auto Show. Sales began in autumn of 2008, and features neither Chrysler's [[Dodge Caravan#Stow'n Go seating|Stow'n Go]] nor [[Dodge Caravan#Swivel 'n Go|Swivel'n Go]] seating systems. When the Chrysler and Dodge badged versions received new features for 2011, not all were shared with the Routan.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/money/autos/reviews/healey/2011-03-17-2011-Volkswagen-Routan-Test-Drive-Healey.htm |title=Volkswagen's Routan has some smooth hustle |date=March 18, 2011 |first=James |last=Healey |work=USAToday |accessdate=April 4, 2016}}</ref>

Total sales as of September 2010 were reported as being under 10,000 units, far lower than the target of 5% of the minivan market.<ref name="allpar-2011">{{cite web|url= http://www.allpar.com/model/m/11-minivans.html |title=2011 Chrysler Town & Country and 2011 Dodge Caravan Minivans |publisher=Allpar |accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref> The Routan was discontinued after the 2013 model year.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.automotive.com/news/not-surprising-news-volkswagen-discontinuing-routan-minivan-sales-132653/ |title=Not-Surprising News: Volkswagen Discontinuing Routan Minivan Sales |first=Jacob |last=Brown |date=March 29, 2013 |work=Automotive.com |accessdate=April 4, 2016}}</ref> A total of 2,500 were produced by Chrysler during the calendar year.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://media.chrysler.com/newsrelease.do?&searchresult=&id=15234&mid= |title=Chrysler Group LLC December 2013 Production Data |date=17 January 2014 |publisher=Chrysler Group LLC |accessdate=April 4, 2016}}</ref>

