'''Liftra''' is an engineering company specialized in lifting and transport equipment for   wind turbines. Since the start-up in 2003 the company has carried out over 500 projects; its   most extensive development project  has been a self-hoisting add-on crane for wind turbines in the +4MW class, that is able to replace 19 Ton components.<ref>{{cite web|title=Liftra - Lifting and Transportation Equipment for the Wind Turbine Industry|url=http://www.power-technology.com/contractors/materials/liftra|publisher=Power Technology|accessdate=13 December 2012}}</ref>

The main office is in [[Aalborg]], Northern Jutland, Denmark with approx. 20 engineers. Offices in Germany, USA, Spain and China.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gill|first=Erin|title=Liftra focuses on rapid loading for offshore projects|url=http://www.windpoweroffshore.com/2012/11/28/liftra_focuses_on_rapid_loading_for_offshore_projects/#.UMmso6z8J8E|publisher=Wind Power Offshore|accessdate=13 December 2012}}</ref>

